article.headline: BYU snaps two-game losing streak
article.story:
RALEIGH, N.C. (AP) -- Erin Thorn had 21 points and eight rebounds
as No. 22 Brigham Young beat North Carolina State 68-57 Saturday. Danielle Cheesman added 20 points for the Cougars (6-2), who
snapped a two-game losing streak.

Kaayla Chones scored 14 for N.C. State (3-5), which fell to 0-3
this season against ranked opponents.

The Wolfpack trailed 31-20 at halftime after hitting 7 of 32
shots (22 percent), including just 1-of-10 3-pointers.

The Cougars were sloppy with the ball, turning it over 19 times,
but the Wolfpack scored just nine points off BYU's turnovers.

Julie Sullivan added 10 points for the Cougars.

Carisse Moody scored 10 for the Wolfpack, the only other N.C.
State player in double figures.

BYU played its third game without second-leading scorer Jennifer
Leitner, who is shooting a team-high 55 percent from the field and
averaging 15.8 points. She has been fighting a series of illnesses.
